        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add redacted MiniMax diagnostic export foundation",
        "body": "Summary:\n\n* Adds a MiniMax diagnostic export model for safe issue-report debugging.\n* Extends LogRedactor to redact MiniMax sk-cp-* and sk-api-* tokens with a prefix-free placeholder.\n* Exports only structural metadata: auth mode, region, strategy/source labels, allowlisted field presence, service count, billing summary presence, and summarized fetch attempt categories.\n* Adds focused tests proving MiniMax tokens, cookie/auth values, and emails are not leaked in redacted output or serialized diagnostics.\n* Documents the safe diagnostic output in docs/minimax.md.\n\nPrivacy:\n\n* No raw API responses or HTML.\n* No raw cookies.\n* No authorization headers.\n* No API tokens.\n* No emails.\n* No user/account/org IDs.\n* No billing history or per-request billing records.\n* No raw error messages in diagnostic export.\n\nValidation:\n\n* swift build --target CodexBarCore: passed\n* swift test --filter \"MiniMaxDiagnosticExport|MiniMaxLogRedactor\": passed, 27 tests in 2 suites\n* full swift test: failed due to unrelated existing OpenAI/Codex background refresh tests:\n\n  * CodexManagedOpenAIWebRefreshTests.swift: \"regular refresh does not await OpenAI web scrape\"\n  * CodexBackgroundRefreshCoalescingTests.swift: \"rapid regular refreshes coalesce concurrent...\"",
